New investment in  commodities
markets , particularly by banks and insurance companies, must be
closely monitored for macroprudential risks, Bundesbank board
member Andreas Dombret said in an editorial in the  Frankfurter
Allgemeine Zeitung .  The Bundesbank would dedicate more attention to the
surveillance of risks in commodities markets, Dombret added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
